# mini-rag core rules (MUST FOLLOW)

## Model calls: HTTP-only

- All LLM + embedding calls **must** go through **OpenAI-compatible HTTP APIs**.
- **Forbidden**: adding local inference / heavy ML deps (e.g. `torch`, `transformers`, HF default stacks, `sentence-transformers`, `onnxruntime`, `faiss`).
- Embeddings must use **`llama_index.embeddings.openai.OpenAIEmbedding`** pointed at SiliconFlow.
- LLM must use **`llama_index.llms.openai.OpenAI`** pointed at DeepSeek.

## Auth + multi-tenancy (Supabase)

- Backend endpoints require `Authorization: Bearer <Supabase JWT>`.
- Never trust `user_id` from request body/querystring.
- All DB reads/writes must be constrained to the authenticated `user_id` (RLS + explicit filters).

## RAG retrieval

- Retrieval must apply metadata filters for **`user_id`** and selected **`kb_ids`**.
- Vector dimension is **1024** (BGE-M3). Do not change without schema migration.

## Structure / ownership

- Keep **UI components** and **business hooks/services** separated:
  - frontend: UI in `src/components/**`, hooks in `src/hooks/**`, infra clients in `src/lib/**`
  - backend: routes in `backend/app/api/**`, services in `backend/app/services/**`, infra in `backend/app/infra/**`

